context: The first union was built on campus in <a0_0><b5_0>1926<b5_0/><a0_0/> as a <a1_0><b6_0>campus community center<b6_0/><a1_0/>. The unions are still the "living rooms" of campus today and include three locations – the Kansas Union and Burge Union at the Lawrence Campus and <a2_0><b7_0>Jayhawk Central<b7_0/><a2_0/> at the Edwards Campus. The <a3_0><b8_0>KU Memorial Unions Corporation<b8_0/><a3_0/> manages the KU Bookstore (with seven locations). The KU Bookstore is the official bookstore of KU. The Corporation also includes KU Dining Services, with more than 20 campus locations, including The Market (inside the Kansas Union) and The Underground (located in Wescoe Hall). The KU Bookstore and KU Dining Services are not-for-profit, with proceeds going back to support student programs, such as <a4_0><b9_0>Student Union Activities<b9_0/><a4_0/>.
